        "create_date":"2017-04-09T09:51:00-07:00",
        "description":"<p><em>Reimagining how dinner is served and how food is eaten, Foad Dizadji-Bahmani presents a series of increasingly complex dishes to navigate and share. Join us for a five course Italian-inspired dining adventure!</em>\n</p>\n<p><em>Limited to 8 participants.</em> SOLD OUT.\n</p>\n<p><strong>Five Italian classics, reimagined:</strong>\n</p>\n<p>prosciutto & melon (bacon and pistachio dust balloons burst over cantaloupes)\n</p>\n<p>bruschetta (ciabatta w/ seven pestos)\n</p>\n<p>calamari (slow braised squid and fried bread w/ bubbling broth)\n</p>\n<p> lasagna (lamb and laurel ragu over a single 8 foot long sheet of pasta (true!) w/ bechamel and parmesan crisps)\n</p>\n<p>tiramisu (suspended ristretto ice cream and mascarpone cream, crumbed Savoiardi)\n</p>",
