        "_sort_start":1510801200,
        "create_date":"2017-11-04T15:16:00-07:00",
        "description":"<p>Join <a href=\"http://www.girlsatlibrary.com/\">GAL</a>, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/hungryrightmeow/\">Lisa Cole</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.days-la.com/\">Days</a> for the newest round of Food to Fiction!\n</p>\n<p>Drawing on the rich tradition of literary translations (think Dostoyevsky, Ferrante, Murakami, <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/02/magazine/the-first-woman-to-translate-the-odyssey-into-english.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&clickSource=story-heading&module=second-column-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news\">the first woman to translate the Odessy</a>) we are hosting an intimate 3 course vegan meal of translations complete with natural wine pairing.  The night will be interactive, informative, and hopefully inspirational!\n</p>\n<p>Tickets sell very quickly: don't wait on getting yours.\n</p>\n<p><em>Limited to 16 seats: SOLD OUT.  Email us for the waitlist.</em>\n</p>",
