        "_sort_publish_date":1536599580,
        "_sort_start":1538247600,
        "create_date":"2018-09-10T10:13:00-07:00",
        "description":"<p>Ike Ike is an introductory workshop to the Japanese flowering arranging technique of Ikebana. This engagement will bring together the idea of space and Days' current iteration of water into a fluid, experiential exploration which will cover the aesthetic variances of the floral art form.\n</p>\n<p>Discussion topics will include minimalism, line form, and overall structure along with philosophical evocations as seen in architecture and environmental design, culminating with each attendee creating a freeform arrangement of their design.\n</p>\n<p>All materials will be provided.\n</p>\n<p>This workshop is limited to 7 people\n</p>\n<p>$35\n</p>\n<p>Reserve your place <a href=\"https://days-la.myshopify.com/collections/event-tickets/products/ikebana-workshop-with-jenn-miller\">here</a>\n</p>",
